      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RULE THE REALM (2) was no match fresh but was much better last time out at this track and trip, sitting on the speed and only being 1.2L away at the finish. Faithfull now hops on board, replacing the apprentice hoop and he has enough speed to cross from the draw. Can go one better. LOONA DAWN (6) ended up 1L off the winner last start at this track and trip in another strong performance. Blinkers come off now and she should be prominent from the draw. Went close last start and this shapes favourably once again. Can get the job done this time around. TRIPLE AR (5) has trialled nicely coming into this at Belmont recently. He debuts on his home deck and Dhurun has been on board the whole way through. The horse who beat him went close to winning in town on Wednesday. Big chance on debut. BELLE OF BONDI (10) won a recent trial at Lark Hill and while she draws awkwardly, it looks a winnable race on debut. GIGI GOGO (7) won't be far away.",
